General
The audit of large companies is not particularly regulated in Germany, and audits are subject to the general regulations • of the Tax Regulation (AO), • of the Financial Administration Act (FVG) and • of the Audit Regulation (BpO).
There are also work aids.
Tax regulation
The provisions of § 193 to 203 AO "Section 4 - External Audit" contain, in particular, rules on the admissibility of an external audit and its factual scope, distribution of responsibilities, form and content of the audit announcement, audit principles, duty of participation of the taxable person and conditions for final discussions as well as for the transmission of the audit report.
