4.5.4 Comparison and evaluation
As a result, large amounts of information are processed automatically in the CZ, including data from VAT audits as well as key figures from balance sheets, profit and loss statements in the system.
The CZ is able to control the selection of risky cases on the basis of a wide range of information.
The same applies to the evaluation and management of VAT audits in general.
In the CZ, the establishment of a special financial office for large enterprises is planned for 2012.
In Germany, the financial administration does not collect comparatively large amounts of data.
Accordingly, it is more difficult to perform these tasks in the same way.
The focus is more on the selection of relevant individual cases.
