5. Conclusions
The cooperation between the two auditors has proved its worth.
This has enabled the necessary knowledge to be gained on the systems used in both countries: in particular: • intra-Community transactions, • risk management at the USt, in particular with regard to the selection of risky transactions, • recovery of VAT receivables and • VAT auditing of large companies.
The audit revealed differences in the strategies for detecting VAT fraud and in the systems explained above.
These findings can be used to improve existing procedures.
They can also be used to initiate a discussion among interested bodies on which audit approaches and strategies can be used to combat fraud, for example in relation to relations within and between the Member States and the European Commission.
The experience and knowledge gained should encourage the joint examination of the administration of the USt in the future.
